            . I live at <placeName id="t18210110-77-crimeloc453">Dalston</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18210110-77-crimeloc453" type="placeName" value="Dalston"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18210110-77-crimeloc453" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210110-77-off451 t18210110-77-crimeloc453"></join>. On the 19th of December in the morning, I discovered the rain-water pipe and trunk were stolen from a building at the back of my house, and found the prisoner in custody next day with it - it was fixed to a green-house attatched to my house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210110-77-person798">
                  JOHN 
                  EASTHAM
               <interp inst="t18210110-77-person798" type="surname" value="EASTHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210110-77-person798" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210110-77-person798" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a plumber. I was at work for Mr. Leigh, and found the pipe gone, it was safe the day before. In the evening as I went to town I followed the prisoner with a bag upon his back, gave him in charge, and asked him what was in his bag? he said it was tin; I found it was the lead - it fitted the place.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210110-77-person799">
